President Donald Trump said that the stock market’s recent upward trajectory shows that traders think his administration’s response to the coronavirus outbreak has been a success.
The market is actually brilliant,” Trump said at a White House news conference on Saturday.
They view it that way.”President Donald Trump speaks during a coronavirus task force briefing Saturday at the White House.
Trump has long treated the stock market as a barometer of his performance and frequently celebrates large gains in the major indexes.
“We had the greatest economy in the history of the world, better than China, better than any country in the world, better than any country’s ever had,” Trump said.